  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nsendRawTransaction and debug.traceTransaction got unexpected results when Geth in the high memory usage.\r\n\r\nsendRawTransaction report [Error:insufficient funds for gas * price + value] even account have enough balance.\r\ndebug.traceTransaction report [Error: required historical state unavailable] even under get current block's internal transaction.\r\nmy geth run --syncmode=fast not --gcmode=archive, and so I understand it can not get history state object before [128](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/eth/api_tracer.go#L52block), but can not understand\r\nwhy can not get current block transaction's state.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nC:\\>geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.8.11-stable\r\nGit Commit: dea1ce052a10cd7d401a5c04f83f371a06fe293c\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.10.2\r\nOperating System: windows\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=C:\\go\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nsendRawTransaction can broatcast transaction\r\ndebug.traceTransaction can get current(latest) block's Tx's all internal transaction\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nsendRawtransaction report [Error:insufficient funds for gas * price + value] even account have enough balance.\r\ndebug.traceTransaction report [Error: required historical state unavailable] even under get current internal transaction.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nwhen geth used 99% RAM , processing block speed delayed,\r\nand some geth functionality not work.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nrun below from scratch, and wait memory  used turn into 99% usage.\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\ngeth.exe  --datadir=data --port 8080 --syncmode \"fast\" --cache=2048 --rpc --rpcport 8545 --rpcaddr \"0.0.0.0\" --rpcapi \"eth,web3,net,shh,personal,debug,miner,rpc,txpool,admin\" --verbosity 3\r\n````\r\nafter restart geth the memory problem gone but\r\nI just to monitor it now.\r\n",
